SIMPLE: embracement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embracement
<hw>Em*brace"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>embrassement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A clasp in the arms;
embrace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dear though chaste <qex>embracements</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>State of being contained; inclosure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the <qex>embracement</qex> of the parts hardly reparable, as
bones.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Willing acceptance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A ready <qex>embracement</qex> of . . . his kindness.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embraceor</ent>⟦br⟧
